	\label{tzero}
\end{figure}
The expression \eqref{temp0} indicates an extremal limit when $ M< \b J$.  We observe that the temperature of BTZ black holes show a similar thermodynamic behaviour to their higher dimensional analogues figure \ref{tzero}. Now we use \eqref{loi1er} and \eqref{MJ} to calculate the entropy
